		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>You strike at a dragon, feeling this weapon thrum in anticipation as the blow sends the dragon reeling.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Weapon</b><b>:</b> Any</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +4d8 critical damage, or +4d12 critical damage against dragons</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Properties:</b>\n<ul>\n<li>The DM chooses a damage type: acid, cold, fire, lightning, or poison. While you are holding the weapon, you have resist 5 against that damage type. Level 14 or 19: Resist 10. Level 24 or 29: Resist 15.</li>\n<li>Your attacks with this weapon against a dragon ignore its resistances.</li>\n</ul></p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power âœ¦ Encounter (Minor Action)</b></p><p><i>Effect:</i> Before the end of the turn, your next attack with this weapon against a dragon gains a +3 power bonus to the damage roll against the target. On a hit, you can also knock the dragon prone.</p><p>Level 14: +6 power bonus.</p><p>Level 19: +9 power bonus.</p><p>Level 24: +12 power bonus.</p><p>Level 29: +15 power bonus.</p>",
